### üß† Step 1: Fit with Conference Themes

IC-DECoN 2025 has multiple tracks, and your topic fits **very naturally** into several of them:

| **Track**                                                                                             | **Relevance to Your Paper**                                                                              |
| ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Data Science and Artificial Intelligence**                                                          | Your system uses AI ‚Äî that‚Äôs a perfect thematic fit.                                                     |
| **Smart Analytics and Machine Learning**                                                              | If you use predictive models for adaptive learning, recommendation systems, etc., this applies directly. |
| **Computing & Communication Technologies**                                                            | If your platform uses cloud/web architecture, or online delivery, it fits.                               |
| **Innovation in Education Systems (possibly under interdisciplinary or emerging technologies track)** | Even though not a major listed track, AI in education is generally accepted under ‚ÄúAI applications.‚Äù     |

‚úÖ **Verdict:** Your paper **fits well** under the **AI / Data Science / Machine Learning** track.
Be sure to emphasize **technical innovation** ‚Äî not just ‚Äúa product idea,‚Äù but what is new in your algorithm, data processing, or adaptive system.

---

### üß© Step 2: What Kind of Papers They‚Äôre Looking For

From the IC-DECoN 2025 call for papers:

* **Type:** Original, unpublished research.
* **Length:** Up to 6 pages (IEEE format).
* **Focus:** Strong technical content ‚Äî algorithms, implementation, or experimental results.
  (Conceptual or survey papers are less favored unless they have clear novelty.)
* **Template:** IEEE conference template (Word or LaTeX).
* **Evaluation:** Papers are reviewed for novelty, technical quality, clarity, and relevance.

---

### üìò Step 3: How to Position Your Paper

For **‚ÄúSkill Pilot: An AI-powered education platform,‚Äù** here‚Äôs how you can structure it to meet IEEE expectations:

| **Section**                               | **What to Emphasize**                                                                                                      |
| ----------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Abstract & Keywords**                   | Concise summary; use technical keywords: ‚Äúadaptive learning,‚Äù ‚ÄúAI recommender,‚Äù ‚Äúpersonalized education,‚Äù etc.             |
| **Introduction**                          | The problem in education technology ‚Äî skill gaps, personalization challenges, and how AI can help.                         |
| **Related Work**                          | Review other AI education platforms (e.g., Coursera‚Äôs AI recommenders, Duolingo‚Äôs ML models) and explain what‚Äôs missing.   |
| **Proposed Method / System Architecture** | Show your **AI model**, architecture (backend, algorithms), or **workflow diagram**. Include flowcharts or block diagrams. |
| **Experiment / Evaluation**               | Metrics: accuracy, user engagement, time reduction, or learning effectiveness.                                             |
| **Results & Discussion**                  | Quantitative or qualitative results. Even small pilot user testing is valuable.                                            |
| **Conclusion & Future Work**              | What‚Äôs next (scaling, adaptive features, integrating with LMS, etc.)                                                       |

